ce:section.ce:para:
Ten kinds of nanoenzymes, including CDCa, GO, CDN, GQDs, GQDy, GQDb, C60-OH, C60, SiO2 and MoS2, have catalysis on the reaction between HAuCl4 and H2O2 to produce gold nanoparticles, the CDCa catalytic system was strongest catalysis, and was chosen for use. It had strong SERS peaks at 240 cm−1, 528 cm−1, 808 cm−1, 1202 cm−1, 1394 cm−1 and 1615 cm−1 (Fig. 2
                        ). The last is most sensitive and was chosen for use. Fig. 2 indicated that CDCa exhibited strong catalysis of the AuNP reaction, and the SERS peak intensity at 1615 cm−1 enhanced with catalyst CDCa increasing when the added VB4r molecular probe concentration was 0.33 μmol/L. When Na+ is added, it can react with PA to form insoluble Na2PA precipitates and restore the catalysis of nanoenzymes. With the increase of Na+ concentration, the produced gold nanoparticles increased and the SERS peak linearly increased, using VB4r as the probe molecule (Fig. 3
                        ). The binding of PA to nanoenzyme surface had an inhibitory effect on the catalytic activity. When PA was added, PA was combined with the nanoenzymes to inhibit their catalysis and reduce the SERS activity of the system. The precipitation of Na2PA was verified to be no catalysis on the reaction between HAuCl4 and H2O2 (Fig. S1).
